# Omegle Video Chat Feature — Implementation Plan

Build the Omegle-style random video chat feature as a full-screen overlay flow accessible from the home page, using LiveKit for video and Redis for matchmaking.

## User Flow (from wireframes)

```
Screen 1: Home page → "Go to video chat" button in sidebar
Screen 2: Overlay modal → Avatar + "Enter your name" + email (pre-filled) + "Create" button
Screen 3: Camera test → Your camera preview + preferences (gender) + "Start Video Call" button
Screen 4: Video call → Your camera (left) + Stranger avatar/video (right) + Skip + Chat via LiveKit
```

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Redis Matchmaking Engine (`packages/cache`)

#### [NEW] [omegle-matchmaker.ts](file:///d:/console-me/packages/cache/src/omegle-matchmaker.ts)

A new `OmegleMatchmaker` class using the same Redis connection pattern as `SessionManager` and `DMChatCache`:

- `setOnline(userId, displayName, email, preference)` → `SET online:omegle:{userId}` with TTL (heartbeat)
- `setOffline(userId)` → removes online key
- `joinQueue(userId, preference)` → `LPUSH` into `omegle:queue:{preference}` and `omegle:queue:any`
- `leaveQueue(userId)` → `LREM` from queue
- `findMatch(userId, preference)` → `RPOP` from matching queue, skip self, create room
- `setMatch(userId1, userId2, roomName)` → `SET match:omegle:{userId1} → {userId2, roomName}` with TTL
- `getMatch(userId)` → lookup current match
- `clearMatch(userId1, userId2)` → remove both match keys
- Singleton `getOmegleMatchmaker()` export

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///d:/console-me/packages/cache/src/index.ts)

Add `export * from "./omegle-matchmaker"` and the singleton getter.

---

### 2. HTTP API — LiveKit Token + Matchmaking (`apps/http`)

#### [NEW] [omegle-controller.ts](file:///d:/console-me/apps/http/src/controller/omegle-controller.ts)

Following existing pattern (`catchAsync`, `AuthRequest`, `AppError`):

- `joinOmegle` — Register user as online, set display name + preference, add to queue, attempt match
  - If match found → generate LiveKit tokens for both users, return room name + token
  - If no match → return `{ status: "searching" }`
- `getToken` — Generate a LiveKit access token for a given room (uses `livekit-server-sdk`)
- `skipMatch` — Clear current match, re-queue user, attempt new match
- `leaveOmegle` — Remove from queue, clear match, set offline

#### [NEW] [omegle-routes.ts](file:///d:/console-me/apps/http/src/routes/omegle-routes.ts)

```
POST /api/v1/omegle/join      → joinOmegle
POST /api/v1/omegle/token     → getToken
POST /api/v1/omegle/skip      → skipMatch
POST /api/v1/omegle/leave     → leaveOmegle
```

All routes behind `protect` middleware.

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///d:/console-me/apps/http/src/index.ts)

Add `import omegleRoutes` and `app.use("/api/v1/omegle", omegleRoutes)`.

#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///d:/console-me/apps/http/package.json)

Add `livekit-server-sdk` as a dependency.

---

### 3. WebSocket Events (`apps/ws`)

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///d:/console-me/apps/ws/src/index.ts)

Add new socket events inside the `io.on("connection")` handler:

| Event | Direction | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| `omegle:matched` | Server → Client | Match found — sends `{ roomName, token, partnerName, partnerId }` |
| `omegle:partner-left` | Server → Client | Partner disconnected from the call |
| `omegle:searching` | Server → Client | Acknowledge search started, no match yet |

The HTTP controller will emit these events via Socket.IO (using `io.to(`user:${userId}`)`) when matches are found. This uses the existing user room system.

---

### 4. Frontend — Omegle UI Components (`apps/web`)

#### [NEW] [omegle-store.ts](file:///d:/console-me/apps/web/src/store/omegle-store.ts)

Zustand store managing the Omegle flow states:
- `step`: `"idle" | "setup" | "camera-test" | "searching" | "connected" | "partner-left"`
- `displayName`, `email`, `preference` (gender: "any" | "male" | "female")
- `roomName`, `token`, `partnerName`, `partnerId`
- Actions: `openOmegle()`, `closeOmegle()`, `setStep()`, `setMatch()`, `reset()`

#### [NEW] [omegle-overlay.tsx](file:///d:/console-me/apps/web/src/components/omegle/omegle-overlay.tsx)

The main full-screen overlay component, renders based on `step` from the store:
- **Step "setup"**: Glassmorphism modal with avatar, name input, email (pre-filled/disabled), "Create" button
- **Step "camera-test"**: Split layout — camera preview (left) + preferences panel (right) with gender selector + "Start Video Call" button
- **Step "searching"**: Animated "Finding match..." state with pulsing animation
- **Step "connected"**: Full video call UI (see below)
- **Step "partner-left"**: Partner left notification + "Find Next" / "Leave" buttons

Premium dark UI with:
- Backdrop blur glassmorphism
- Smooth fade/slide transitions between steps
- Gradient accents (purple → cyan matching existing app vibe)
- Micro-animations on buttons, status indicators

#### [NEW] [video-room.tsx](file:///d:/console-me/apps/web/src/components/omegle/video-room.tsx)

The actual video call component using LiveKit:
- **Left panel**: Your camera feed (large)
- **Right panel**: Stranger's camera/avatar + their name + Skip button + LiveKit Data Channel chat
- Uses `@livekit/components-react` for `<LiveKitRoom>`, `<VideoTrack>`, `<AudioTrack>`
- Controls: Mute mic, mute camera, skip, end call
- Chat panel at the bottom (using LiveKit's built-in data messages)

#### [NEW] [use-omegle.ts](file:///d:/console-me/apps/web/src/hooks/use-omegle.ts)

Custom hook combining:
- The omegle store
- Socket.IO listeners for `omegle:matched`, `omegle:partner-left`
- API calls to `/api/v1/omegle/*` endpoints
- Camera/mic permission management via `navigator.mediaDevices`

#### [MODIFY] [home page.tsx](file:///d:/console-me/apps/web/src/app/(root)/home/page.tsx)

Add "Go to Video Chat" button in the left sidebar nav, below the existing nav items. Clicking it opens the omegle overlay via `useOmegleStore().openOmegle()`.

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///d:/console-me/apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx)

Mount `<OmegleOverlay />` globally (same pattern as `<PostModal />` and `<ChatPopover />`).

